article.headline: Northwestern 67, Texas-Pan American 56
article.story: EVANSTON, Ill. (AP) -- Kevin Coble scored 18 points and Northwestern set a school record with its 11th non-conference win of the season in a 67-56 victory over Texas-Pan American on Wednesday night. Tim Doyle scored 12 of his 17 points in the first half for the Wildcats (13-14), who snapped a two-game losing streak and improved to 11-3 outside the Big Ten. They'll try to improve on their 2-11 conference mark Saturday against Purdue. Brian Burrell scored 16 of his game-high 24 points in the second half for Texas-Pan American. The Broncs (13-13) have lost three of their last four games, and now are 1-10 on the road. Getting a pair of 3-pointers each from Burrell and Paul Stoll in the opening minutes of the second half, Texas-Pan American pulled within 44-42 with 11:12 to play. But Northwestern weathered that 13-2 run and went on a 13-4 run of its own, pushing the lead back into double figures on Coble's 3-pointer with 5:15 remaining. That gave the Wildcats a 57-46 advantage that was good enough to keep the Broncs at bay. After trading baskets with the Broncs for the first six minutes of the game, Northwestern took the lead for good when Doyle's third layup gave the Wildcats a 13-11 advantage. The 6-5 senior scored in a variety of ways in the post, on the break and with a 3-pointer that gave the Wildcats a 28-17 lead, notching 12 of his points in the first half. Northwestern made the most of Texas-Pan American's first-half mistakes, scoring 10 points off six turnovers. Holding the Broncs to 9-of-21 shooting, Northwestern was up 37-26 at the half. Jason Okrzesik and Jeff Ryan added 11 and 10 points off the bench, respectively, for the Wildcats. Okrzesik led the way at the foul line, going 9-of-9 as Northwestern finished 21-of-24 in the game. Northwestern set its previous record of 10 non-conference wins in the 1993-94 season.
